Bring 150ml/5fl oz water to the boil, add the salt and stir. Then add the oats and reduce the heat.Cover and simmer for 15-20 minutes, then remove from the heat and put into a bowl.  Preheat the oven to 180C/350F/Gas 4.Add the bulgar wheat and any water remaining from soaking to the bowl.Heat the olive oil in a frying pay, and saute the garlic, add the onions and pimentos and cook until soft.Put into a bowl along with the remaining ingredients. Season to taste, mix well and put in a greased baking dish.  Bake 1 hour.